Manchester City striker Sergio Aguero has been named the Barclays Premier League player of the month for November after scoring three goals in four appearances.

The Argentina star netted the winner in the derby against Manchester United, as well as scoring twice in the 2-2 draw at Queens Park Rangers.

Aguero, 26, has been on fire for City so far this campaign and has scored 14 Premier League goals in just 15 appearances.

